article.headline: Alaska-Anchorage 62, Louisiana Tech 57
article.story: ANCHORAGE, Alaska -- Kenny Barker scored 23 points and Alaska-Anchorage hung on to defeat Louisiana Tech 62-57 on Saturday for seventh place in the Great Alaska Shootout. Barker's 3-pointer broke a 51-all tie and gave the Seawolves (1-5) the lead for good with 6:46 remaining. The Division II school had trouble getting off shots against the taller Bulldogs and committed eight turnovers in the first 8 minutes. But Louisiana Tech shot just 33 percent for the half, including 1-of-8 on 3-pointers, and needed 11 free throws to lead 30-29 at halftime. Kyle Gibson hit two free throws to pull Louisiana Tech within 60-57 with 9.6 seconds left. The Bulldogs (2-4) fouled Barker on the inbound pass and he hit both ends of a one-on-one to seal it. Gibson led Louisiana Tech with 17 points. Kenneth Cooper had 15.
